A car bomb attack at the Hilton hotel in Taba killed 23 Israelis and injured over 100 people of various nationalities.
The explosion, suspected to be orchestrated by Hamas, coincided with Jewish holidays.
Additional car bomb explosions in tourist camps in Sinai resulted in more casualties.
Despite warnings, many Israelis continued to visit Sinai, a popular destination.
Israeli officials suspected terrorism and facilitated evacuations.
The tragic events unfolded amidst heightened tensions in the region, with Palestinians also facing casualties.
Efforts were made to assist affected individuals and ensure their safe return to Israel.
